movies.title: The Shawshank Redemption
movies.description: Two imprisoned men bond over a number of years, finding solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.

movies.title: The Godfather
movies.description: The aging patriarch of an organized crime dynasty transfers control to his reluctant son.

movies.title: The Dark Knight
movies.description: When the menace known as the Joker emerges, Batman must accept his greatest psychological and physical tests.

movies.title: The Godfather Part II
movies.description: The early life and career of Vito Corleone in 1920s New York is portrayed, while his son expands the family empire.

movies.title: 12 Angry Men
movies.description: A jury holdout attempts to prevent a miscarriage of justice by forcing his colleagues to reconsider the evidence.

movies.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King
movies.description: Gandalf and Aragorn lead the World of Men against Sauron's army to draw his gaze from Frodo and Sam.

movies.title: Schindler's List
movies.description: In German-occupied Poland during World War II, Oskar Schindler saves the lives of more than a thousand Jews.

movies.title: Pulp Fiction
movies.description: The lives of two mob hitmen, a boxer, and two diner bandits intertwine in a series of tales.

movies.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring
movies.description: A meek Hobbit and his eight companions set out on a journey to destroy the powerful One Ring.

movies.title: Il buono, il brutto, il cattivo
movies.description: A bounty hunting scam joins two men in an uneasy alliance against a third in a race to find gold.
